[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing existing tests**\n\nI'm thinking that existing tests probably passed, but I'm curious about the Anonymous4 test and its relation to the newFileScopedGeneratedExtension. It seems like it reflects on the ExtensionDescriptorHolder.descriptor public field? I wonder if metadata for the test class is necessary. It could fail unless it's included. Maybe they added the test just to gather metadata for the library. I find this situation intriguing!\n\n**Considering conditional mode challenges**\n\nIn conditional mode, the user-code filter determines which classes are considered application code, focusing on org.apache for library conditions. However, this could cause issues with the target org_apache being excluded due to the extra-filter. I'm unsure if Forge will merge generated metadata externally, and whether tests ran in native might utilize these agent-generated metadata. I think I can avoid needing reflection metadata by access a class in the org.apache package reflectively, but the public API requires that the generated message class extends GeneratedMessage from org.apache.\n\n**Inspecting jar files**\n\nI think I need to inspect the client jar now. It seems like that could help resolve the issue. I wonder if the context jar only includes source files, but maybe the shaded jar contains generated classes that aren't in the source. I should definitely use Maven to download the appropriate binary. Let’s see how I can navigate this to make sure I get the right files!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07a4f13acf7a1961016a0f4d06a5f881928726a2ce79e3cab6\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqD00azgJ-xggNaeNvISr_B1WQrtGSsdj05Im7yBkr3is4_XUrjgV3E99BYy5-v1kl77KuWh9NkyAZFt7SexwLpTOQQTl90oWyhMn856VF3lpfiFx_3Ia4sDGtKJaVhlL2a-U8Igk7O_5r2M_YVYVAbFHqzmcfmLdPvFAJ6_QmiBH4-fNstK3cb42K0HontZfFyNOt3t0mrMnM5LHjvJsPpq5kQ5YfcZCuXkNw1XMnPAEjkH6poWsA935un