[thinking] **Analyzing native-image builds**
[thinking] 
[thinking] It's important to note that a native-image build of a test app could have runtime issues if reflection is invoked on methods not included in the metadata. I wonder if native-image maintains strict metadata for public methods. Class.getMethod could still throw NoSuchMethodException for unregistered methods. If the class is interacted with normally, maybe some reflection metadata for public methods would be present, but not always. Though, there might be exceptions for application classes. Native-image doesn’t include all reflection metadata, and static analysis can play a role in registering calls.
[thinking] 
