[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm unsure if Forge will utilize the generated metadata. Should I add the build argument `-H:ReflectionConfigurationResources`? That seems forbidden. Existing tests incorporate dynamic targets on test classes, which might be accepted due to the metadata supporting them. I probably shouldn’t overthink this. There's a mention of `AccessorBackedMessage` where the nested class name includes a `$`, but is that applicable since the rule states to avoid `$` in test class names? Inner classes might be an exception. It seems the dynamic-access class may map to the library report correctly.
